Webhook event types
TikTok offers two main categories of Webhook events related to TikTok accounts:

Post publishing events.
These events are related to the publishing of video or photo posts on a TikTok account. They are triggered when posts are published through specific API endpoints and provide updates on the status of published content throughout its lifecycle.
Comment updates events.
These events are associated with comments on posts associated with your TikTok account. They notify you of new comments or changes to existing comments on your posts, allowing you to monitor and manage user interactions.
Each category serves a specific purpose, enabling you to receive real-time updates on different aspects of TikTok account activity and user engagement. By leveraging these webhook events, you can stay in sync with TikTok platform activities.

To learn more about how to create the configurations for these Webhook events , see Subscribe to TikTok account Webhook events via Webhooks API.





















Post publishing events
Post publishing events provide you with real-time updates on the status of content published via specific TikTok API endpoints. These events are triggered only for posts that are published through /business/video/publish/ or /business/photo/publish/. The event types you'll receive include:

post.publish.failed
post.publish.complete
post.publish.publicly_available
post.publish.no_longer_publicly_available
Note
To configure a Webhook callback URL for your developer app, use the Webhook API endpoint /business/webhook/update/.

Post publishing life cycle
The following table describes the life cycle that a post goes through after an API request has been made to publish the post and the expected time between receiving notifications for each stage:

Stage	Event	Description	Expected Time Delay
1*one of the two	post.publish.failed	Post publishing failed due to format constraint violations or post URL being blocked before download completion.	Not deterministic - depends on file size and network conditions. In general, 30 minutes should be sufficient to download a 1GB post file.
post.publish.complete	Post publishing completed - file format constraints were met and no issues in downloading file from provided URL.	Not deterministic - depends on file size and network conditions. In general, 30 minutes should be sufficient to download a 1GB post file.
2	post.publish.publicly_available	Post published has gone through moderation and is distributed for public viewership on TikTok.	In normal cases will take at most 2 minutes, but may take longer if manual moderation is required.
3*conditional	post.publish.no_longer_publicly_available	Post published is no longer available for public viewership on TikTok. This may be because of subsequent moderation or because the user has turned the post to friends-only/private viewership.	N/A - may occur at any time after a post has become publicly available
Post publishing event types
post.publish.failed
Fired when the post uploaded fails to upload to TikTok.

Event content
Field	Data Type	Description
publish_id
string
An identifier for the requested publish to TikTok action
reason
string
A machine-parsable string representing the reason for the failure, listed in the "Failure reasons" section below.
publish_type
string
Publish type. The allowed enum value: DIRECT_PUBLISH (To directly publish the post to your TikTok Account).
Failure reasons
Reason	Description
file_format_check_failed
TikTok server is able to download the post material but identifies that the post file format did not meet the file format specifications.
This is not a retryable error.
duration_check_failed
TikTok server is able to download the video material but identifies that the video file format did not meet the duration constraint - min 3 seconds long, max 60 seconds long.
This is not a retryable error.
frame_rate_check_failed
TikTok server is able to download the video material but identifies that the video file format did not meet the frame rate specifications - min 23 FPS, max 60 FPS.
This is not a retryable error.
picture_size_check_failed
TikTok server is able to download the post material but identifies that the post file format did not meet the picture resolution specifications - min height and width being 360p.
This is not a retryable error.
internal
Some parts of TikTok server may be currently unavailable.
This is a retryable error.
video_pull_failed
TikTok server encountered a connection error while downloading the specified video resource, or the download is terminated since it cannot be completed within the one hour timeout.
Check if the supplied URL is publicly accessible or bandwidth-limited. If partner is certain that the URL is valid, a retry is recommended.
photo_pull_failed
TikTok server encountered a connection error while downloading the specified photo resource, or the download is terminated since it can not be completed within the one hour timeout.
Check if the supplied URL is publicly accessible or bandwidth-limited. If developers are certain that the URL is valid, a retry is recommended.
auth_removed
This TikTok creator has removed the developer's access while the download/uploading is being processed, so the publishing effort must be terminated.
Retry should not be done.
spam_risk_too_many_posts
This TikTok creator has created too many posts within the last 24 hours via API.
Try to publish the posts from the TikTok Mobile App.
spam_risk_user_banned_from_posting
This TikTok creator is banned from making new posts.
spam_risk_text
The description text has risky or spammy contents, so the publishing attempt is terminated. .
spam_risk
TikTok determines that the post has a high spamming risk and rejects the publishing attempt. This may be a result of:
Making publishing attempts too frequently
Other risky in-app user behaviors
